max skill and about 7 hq in bank.. but like others... i am not willing to risky a hq bear for something that might not even work.<P>but if someone wants me to try  using theirs on xegony just give me a tell<P>     camile xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">ZoWn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Quiver Pattern + HQ Bear Pelt<P>------------------<BR>---<BR>*/* OWN<BR>---<P><BR><p>[This message has been edited by ZoWn (edited 12-04-1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Tinwin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">A small update to this.  I made 3 attempts at Fleeting Quivers over the weekend with (as I have not seen a recipe for this form of quiver);<P>HQ Bear Pelt + Fleeting Quiver Pattern<BR>MQ Bear Pelt + Fleeting Quiver Pattern<BR>MQ Cat Pelt + Fleeting Quiver Pattern<P>All of which gave the message that these do not combine in that combination.<P>I should have used the HQ Bear with a normal Quiver pattern but I chose the wrong pattern from my backpack.  Next one I get though will be used in the pursuit of experimentation.<P>Tinwin<BR>Tailoring 75</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Tinwin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Just a quick update.  The recipe for making a Quiver of<P>HQ Bear Pelt + Quiver Pattern<P>does NOT work.  The good old do not combine in those quantities message pops up.<P>So we seem to be back to the drawing board on that one. <P>Tinwin<BR>Erolissi Marr<BR>Tailor 78</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Asherr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">  Is it possible that you need an MQ or HQ cat or wolf pelt for quivers?  A bear pelt for a backpack makes sense as a backpack in a large item, but quivers and small to medium items.  Thoughts?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Taft</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">When did HQ bear pelts become worth so damn much?  I used to get them all the time in Misty Thicket and sold dozens of them to VENDORS (before I was a tailor) because NO ONE wanted to buy them.<P><BR>Taft</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Yamen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">It is impossible to make (all)quivers right now, it has something to do with a bug or the trade skill is partially broken.<BR>Other broken armor:<BR>Studded<BR>   tunic<BR>   cloak<BR>   belt<BR>   shoulder pads<BR>Reinforced<BR>   mask<P>I hope this saves some people money and I'm sorry that I didn't find this thread sooner.<P>Yamen, loyal druid of karana<BR>(cazic-thule server)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
